children.title: Inspect parallel and angular alignment
children.hint: 8.3.6.4  Parallel and angular alignment of the pump and driver shall be inspected during the annual test, and any misalignment shall be corrected.

children.title: Pressure relief valve downstream of fittings does not exceed system rated pressure, and set to relieve at the correct pressure and close below pressure setting
children.hint: 13.5.6.2.2 The inspection shall verify that the pressure downstream of the relief valve fittings in the fire pump discharge piping does not exceed the pressure for which the system components are rated. 13.5.6.2.3 During the annual fire pump flow test, the pressure relief valve shall be verified to be correctly adjusted and set to relieve at the correct pressure and to close below that pressure setting.

children.title: Electrical connections inspected without opening energized pump controller
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.2.1 Electrical connections shall be inspected annually and repaired as necessary to the extent that such work can be completed without opening an energized electric-motor-driven fire pump controller.

children.title: Supervisory signal circuitry tested for high cooling water temperature
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.8 Supervisory signal circuitry shall be tested annually for high cooling water temperature.

children.title: Suction screens inspected and cleaned after water flow
children.hint: 8.3.3.15 Suction Screens. After the waterflow portions of the annual test or fire protection system activations, the suction screens shall be inspected and cleared of any debris or obstructions

children.title: Flexible hoses/connection inspected for cracks and leaks
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.11 All flexible hoses and connections shall be inspected annually for cracks and leaks.

children.title: Circulating water filters replaced
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.21 Circulating water filters shall be replaced annually.

children.title: Inspect pump shaft end play
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.1 Shaft movement or end play shall be checked annually with the pump operating.

children.title: Inspect accuracy of pressure gauges and sensors, and change as needed
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.21  The accuracy of pressure gauges and sensors shall be inspected annually and replaced or recalibrated when more than 5% out of calibration.

children.title: Inspect pump coupling alignment
children.hint: 8.3.6.4  Parallel and angular alignment of the pump and driver shall be inspected during the annual test, and any misalignment shall be corrected.

children.title: Printed circuit boards inspected for corrosion without opening energized pump controller
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.4.1 Printed circuit boards (PCBs) shall be inspected annually for corrosion to the extent that such work can be completed without opening an energized electric-motor-driven fire pump controller.

children.title: Cable/wire insulation inspected for cracking without opening energized pump controller
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.5.1 Cable and/or wire insulation shall be inspected annually for cracking to the extent that such work can be completed without opening an energized electric-motor-driven fire pump controller

children.title: Alarm indicating (visual and functional) operating correctly
children.hint: 8.3.3.10  Alarm conditions shall be simulated by activating alarm circuits at alarm sensor locations, and all such local or remote alarm indicating devices (visual and audible) shall be observed for operation.

children.title: Test electronic control module (ECM); confirm functioning correctly
children.hint: 8.3.3.13  Where engines utilize electronic fuel management control systems, the backup electronic control module (ECM) and the primary and redundant sensors for the ECM shall be tested annually.

children.title: Inspect sacrificial anode; replace as needed
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.19  The condition of sacrificial anodes shall be checked annually and replaced as necessary

children.title: Lubricate bearings and change as needed
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.3 Pump and motor bearings and couplings shall be greased annually or as required.

children.title: Pertinent notifications made before testing
children.hint: 4.1.4  Notification of System Shutdown or Testing. The property owner or designated representative shall notify the authority having jurisdiction, the fire department, if required, and the alarm-receiving facility before testing or shutting down a system or its supply.

children.title: Pump run for minimum of 10 minutes?
children.hint: 8.3.2.3 The electric pump shall run a minimum of 10 minutes.

children.title: Confirm fire pump starts in response to pressure drop
children.hint: 8.3.2.2 The test shall be conducted by starting the pump automatically.

children.hint: 8.3.2.9 (1) The pertinent visual observations or adjustments specified in the following checklists shall be conducted while the pump is running: (c) Inspect the pump packing glands for slight discharge. (d) Adjust gland nuts if necessary.

children.title: Record pressure switch (or pressure transducer) reading.  Compare to pump discharge gauge
children.hint: 8.3.2.9 (1)(g) The pertinent visual observations or adjustments specified in the following checklists shall be conducted while the pump is running: Record pressure switch or pressure transducer reading and compare to the pump discharge gauge.

children.title: Check packing boxes, bearings, or pump casing for overheating
children.hint: 8.3.2.9(1)(f)  Inspect packing boxes, bearings, or pump casing for overheating.

children.title: Pump with electronic pressure sensors, record highest and lowest pressure from controller event log
children.hint: 8.3.2.9 (1)(h) The pertinent visual observations or adjustments specified in the following checklists shall be conducted while the pump is running: For pumps that use electronic pressure sensors to control the fire pump operation, record the current pressure and the highest and the lowest pressure shown on the fire pump controller event log.

children.title: Check for unusual noise or vibration
children.hint: 8.3.2.9(1)(e) Inspect for unusual noise or vibration.

children.title: Circulation (casing) relief valve functions correctly
